(gdb) x /32xh 0x50001000
0x50001000:	0x0000	0x0002	0x0004	0x0006	0x0008	0x000a	0x000c	0x000e
0x50001010:	0x0010	0x0012	0x0014	0x0016	0x0018	0x001a	0x001c	0x001e
0x50001020:	0x0020	0x0022	0x0024	0x0026	0x0028	0x002a	0x002c	0x002e
0x50001030:	0x0030	0x0032	0x0034	0x0036	0x0038	0x003a	0x003c	0x003e

so offset is the offset from base registered as start addr.

in memory code instruction look like F8DFF000
when used to disassemble as arm thumb2
need to be F000 F8DF
ldr.w pc, [pc, #0]
will load the next memory address relative to current pc. perhaps its because when load it, pc already go to next?
